---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="The Evolution of EduMyna"
  description="Twelve years of building education infrastructure at scale. From India's first PPP incubator to university-integrated programs to open-source platforms. This is how EduMyna emerged."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50 border-b border-slate-200">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-4xl py-20">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 bg-blue-50 rounded-full mb-4">
          2009 - 2024
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight">
          Twelve years of learning what actually works in education
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
          EduMyna didn't start with a business plan. It emerged from 12 years of
          building education programs at scale—supporting 500+ startups, creating 3,000+ jobs,
          partnering with governments and tech giants, and learning what students actually need to succeed.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-sm text-slate-500">
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">500+</div>
            <div>Startups Supported</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">3,139</div>
            <div>Jobs Created</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">₹45Cr</div>
            <div>Raised by Alumni</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">12</div>
            <div>Years Operating</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <Container>
    <!-- The Journey -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-8">The Mission Never Changed</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Since 2009, the deeply-held desire has been consistent: <strong>helping others enable themselves</strong>.
          What changed was our understanding of how to do it effectively.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Timeline -->
      <div class="mt-16 space-y-12">

        <!-- 2009-2012: The Dream -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 bg-blue-100 rounded mb-2">
              2009-2012
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              The Dream: Building a Silicon Coast
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              It started with a vision—create a "Silicon Coast" in Kerala by enabling entrepreneurs.
              MobME submitted a proposal to the Government of India to set up India's first
              Public-Private-Partnership incubator.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-4 space-y-2">
              <div class="text-sm text-slate-700">
                <strong>Commitment:</strong> 10,000 sq ft space, ₹2.5Cr grant, support 48 startups over 5 years
              </div>
              <div class="text-sm text-slate-700">
                <strong>Entity:</strong> Startup Village (ITIH-TBI), Kerala's first tech incubator
              </div>
              <div class="text-sm text-slate-700">
                <strong>Structure:</strong> Non-profit society under Travancore Societies Act
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2012-2014: Physical Reality -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-green-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-green-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 bg-green-100 rounded mb-2">
              2012-2014
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              Physical Startup Village: Learning What Works
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              The Kochi campus opened. Students flocked in. We ran massive programs—distributed 10,000 Raspberry Pis,
              gave Startup Boxes (MacBooks + iPads) to teams, took cohorts to Silicon Valley, partnered with MIT for Fab Labs.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900">75</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-700">Startups (Physical)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900">425</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-700">Startups (Virtual)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900">₹45Cr</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-700">Funding Raised</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900">3,139</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-700">Jobs Created</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-4 border-l-4 border-green-500">
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium mb-2">ROI to Government:</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                <li>• For every ₹1 invested by govt, ₹9.68 was invested into startups by investors</li>
                <li>• For every ₹15,309 invested by govt, 1 new job was created</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Critical Learning (2013):</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-amber-800">
                We could only provide meaningful value to <strong>student startups</strong>.
                Everyone else had better options. In Jan 2015, we made the call: student startups only.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2015-2017: Digital Pivot -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-purple-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-purple-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-purple-700 bg-purple-100 rounded mb-2">
              2015-2017
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              SV.CO: The Digital Transformation
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Physical didn't scale. We went fully digital—SV.CO was born. Removed mobile apps,
              went web-only. Built timelines for every startup, created progression models (5/10/20/30 stages),
              ran cohort-based programs online.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-400 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="font-medium text-slate-900">April 2016: Spun off as private company</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-slate-600">Team moved to Bangalore, went "developers only"</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-400 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="font-medium text-slate-900">June 2017: Silicon Valley cohort trip</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-slate-600">Entire team + students. Post-trip: major strategic clarity</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-400 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="font-medium text-slate-900">Nov 2017: The Startup → Skills Pivot</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-slate-600">Realized students needed skills more than startup advice</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2018: Developer Focus -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-orange-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-orange-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-orange-700 bg-orange-100 rounded mb-2">
              2018
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              Developer Education & University Integration
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              The year of experiments. Tried everything—Product School (subscription model),
              Hackkar (job placement for tier 2/3 college developers), university-integrated courses with Apple and Facebook.
            </p>

            <div class="grid gap-3">
              <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-3 border-l-4 border-orange-400">
                <div class="font-medium text-orange-900 text-sm mb-1">Apple iOS School @ Manipal</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-orange-700">First university-integrated offering. Credited elective model.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-3 border-l-4 border-orange-400">
                <div class="font-medium text-orange-900 text-sm mb-1">Facebook VR Program (School of Innovation)</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-orange-700">Fully Facebook-funded. Built Coach Dashboard for external faculty.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-3 border-l-4 border-orange-400">
                <div class="font-medium text-orange-900 text-sm mb-1">Hackkar Experiment</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-orange-700">Learned timing mismatch: companies need year-round, students graduate once.</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Realization (Nov-Dec 2018):</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                The platform we'd built was comparable to Teachable.com (valued at $100M+).
                We could separate the framework from the SV.CO brand and turn it into SaaS.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-blue-600 mt-2">
                <strong>Dec 5, 2018:</strong> pupilfirst.com domain registered
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2019-2021: Pupilfirst -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-indigo-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-indigo-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-700 bg-indigo-100 rounded mb-2">
              2019-2021
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              Pupilfirst: Education Infrastructure as SaaS
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Built the admin interface for third-party clients. Replaced the student dashboard.
              Created rich curriculum system (WordPress Gutenberg-style). Shipped 316 commits in a day.
              Universities started deploying. The infrastructure was proven.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-indigo-900 mb-3">Technical Achievement:</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-indigo-700 space-y-2">
                <li>✓ First-class admin interface (not just backend tools)</li>
                <li>✓ Large-scale ReasonML & ReasonReact usage</li>
                <li>✓ Rich content blocks for curriculum design</li>
                <li>✓ Multi-university deployments</li>
                <li>✓ Open-source core infrastructure</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-4 italic">
              Role: Co-founder (continues to present)
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2021-2022: Vision Divergence -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-rose-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-rose-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700 bg-rose-100 rounded mb-2">
              2021-2022
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              The Split: Different Paths, Same Mission
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Vision differences with the primary Pupilfirst co-founder. The mission remained—fixing
              higher education at scale—but the approach diverged. Time to explore a different path.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-rose-50 rounded-lg p-4 border-l-4 border-rose-400">
              <p class="text-sm text-rose-900 font-medium mb-2">Core Belief Unchanged:</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-rose-700">
                Education is a complex, multi-stakeholder system. No single company can solve it alone.
                It requires patience, long-term focus, and socially conscious investors willing to
                optimize for impact over quick returns.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2022-2024: The Second Design -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-teal-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-teal-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-teal-700 bg-teal-100 rounded mb-2">
              2022-2024
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">
              The Second Design: Testing the Pedagogy
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Partnered with Dr. Aruna Kesavan (former Harvard lecturer, astrophysicist).
              Started HowToCBC, later rebranded to The Second Design. Worked with edupreneurs
              globally. Developed and tested RealWorldReady program.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-900">1,500+</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-teal-700">Learners Reached</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-900">100+</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-teal-700">Sessions Conducted</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-900">10/10</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-teal-700">Perfect Rating (2-week course)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-900">Maven</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-teal-700">Top 75 (from 2000+ applicants)</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-900 mb-2">RealWorldReady Program:</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-teal-700 mb-3">
                A practice-heavy program teaching students agency, systems thinking, and how to
                actually navigate careers. Not lectures—real work.
              </p>
              <div class="text-sm text-teal-800">
                <strong>Outcome:</strong> 63% of attendees rated sessions 10/10. Students reported
                clarity on goals, confidence to act, improved communication.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-2">Clients & Partners:</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-600">
                McDonald's, IMG Academy, Glovo, FOSS United, ed-tech unicorns, global CBC platforms
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2024: EduMyna -->
        <div class="relative pl-8 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
          <div class="absolute -left-2 top-0 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-600 rounded-full ring-4 ring-blue-100"></div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 bg-blue-100 rounded mb-2">
              2024+
            </span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3">
              EduMyna: Taking It to Millions
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-lg">
              All the learnings converge here. The infrastructure (Pupilfirst LMS forked, open-sourced).
              The pedagogy (RealWorldReady tested, proven). The partnerships (governments, universities, corporations).
              The mission (unchanged for 15 years).
            </p>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-blue-200">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-blue-900 mb-4">What EduMyna Does:</h4>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>EduMyna LMS:</strong> Open-source education platform (forked from Pupilfirst)
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>Funds The Second Design:</strong> To run RealWorldReady programs
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>Student Acquisition:</strong> Marketing to bring learners to programs
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>New Tech Products:</strong> Tools for running education at scale
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>Policy Work:</strong> Interventions to fix systemic education issues
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2"></div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                    <strong>Government Partnerships:</strong> Working at state & national level
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 p-6 bg-slate-900 rounded-xl text-white">
              <p class="text-lg font-medium mb-3">
                "I've spent 12 years building education infrastructure at scale. I know what works.
                I've partnered with governments and tech giants. I've tested the pedagogy.
                Now I'm building the platform that takes this to millions."
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
                — Gautam, Founder
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why This Matters -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-12 border border-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">
        Why This Journey Matters
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div>
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Proven at Scale</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Not theory. Not a prototype. This comes from supporting 500+ startups,
            3000+ jobs, ₹45Cr raised, partnerships with Facebook, Apple, and 4 state governments.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Battle-Tested Pivots</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Navigated major transitions successfully—physical to digital, startups to skills,
            proprietary to open-source. Know when to persist, when to pivot.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6V4m0 2a2 2 0 100 4m0-4a2 2 0 110 4m-6 8a2 2 0 100-4m0 4a2 2 0 110-4m0 4v2m0-6V4m6 6v10m6-2a2 2 0 100-4m0 4a2 2 0 110-4m0 4v2m0-6V4" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Systems Thinking</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Understand education as a complex system—teachers, incentives, institutions, policy.
            Not just building software. Building change infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto my-32 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
        Want to be part of this?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
        EduMyna is raising funding to take these learnings to millions of students.
        If you're an investor, partner, or just someone who believes education can be better, let's talk.
      </p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="px-8 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition"
        >
          Get in Touch
        </a>
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="px-8 py-3 bg-slate-100 text-slate-700 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-200 transition"
        >
          About Gautam
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </Container>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Timeline responsive adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .relative.pl-8 {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
